item.title: Report E-2025040379
item.description:
Report E-2025040379

Identified by scraper @ 2025-05-09T12:25:20+00:00

  • Incident Date: 2025-04-14
  • City: FIFE
  • State: WA
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: R & L CARRIERS, INC.
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 5000
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: On April 14, 2025, one (1) 5-gallon pail of UN3109 was punctured and released approximately three (3) cups of product to the dock floor. R+L Carriers retained Cura Emergency Services, LC who dispatched a crew from GrayMar Environmental Services (GES) to remediate the site. The crew identified the one (1) damaged 5-gallon jug of product, which was placed into its own 55-gallon vented poly drum for waste. The release had been cleaned by terminal personnel, and the jug of product had been patched and plugged. The spent absorbents were placed into one (1) 55-gallon poly drum that was placed into the terminal's dumpster. Crews inspected the dumpster and found that all impacted absorbents were successfully containerized in the one (1) 55-gallon drum and had not released to the rest of the dumpster, so crews removed the 55-gallon drum. The impacted absorbents were transferred into one (1) new 55-gallon, vented poly drum, and the damaged drum was cut up with hand tools for waste. Crews utilized absorbent pads and cleaning agents to wipe down the impacted dock floor. One (1) 55-gallon vented poly drum of any spent absorbents, cleanup debris, and the cut-up drum was staged alongside the one (1) 55-gallon drum that contained the one (1) impacted jug.

Identified by scraper @ 2025-05-09T12:25:20+00:00

  • Incident Date: 2025-04-07
  • City: SEATTLE
  • State: WA
  • Report Type: Undeclared Shipment with no Release
  • Mode Of Transportation: Air
  • Carrier/Reporter: FEDERAL EXPRESS CORPORATION
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 0
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: On 4/7/2025 at approximately 1200 hours, Dangerous Goods Administration received a call from Employee 2593663 at the station location in Seattle, reporting undeclared dangerous goods. The shipment consists of one paper FedEx envelope that contained one fiberboard box with two small bottles of fragrance inside of it. The shipment was discovered after a failed delivery attempt and during the preparation for shipping to the Overgoods facility. One of the bottles displayed the flammable GHS label. The shipment has very minimal information and most the commodity information is estimated. The shipment is being held, pending an investigation by the FAA.
